Version of R used: 4.3.3

Project

Overview


Goal(s):

This script will go through SNP filtering steps using a vcf file to retain the best possible SNPs.


Details about files and pipeline:


File information

  • Prior to this script steps 01 to 07 (up to 07_populations call SNPs) on my GitHub were completed. The vcf file from populations was generated with the maximum observed heterozygosity set to 0.5.

File name : populations-HO0.5.snps.vcf

Generate a population map file (similar format to STACKS)

popmap <- data.frame(id=colnames(vcf@gt)[2:length(colnames(vcf@gt))], pop=rep(1,46))


Step 2: Genotype depth and Genotype quality

This is a completely unfiltered vcf file (SNPs were called in populations with no filters). We will start by visualizing the depth of sequencing and genotype quality.

## When there is no filters set, the function will show visuals
hard_filter(vcf)
## no depth cutoff provided, exploratory visualization will be generated.

## no genotype quality cutoff provided, exploratory visualization will be generated.

From the histograms we can see that setting depth to 5 and quality to 20 is reasonable for this vcf.

vcf_filtered <- hard_filter(vcf, depth = 5, gq = 20)
## 28.98% of genotypes fall below a read depth of 5 and were converted to NA
## 0.8% of genotypes fall below a genotype quality of 20 and were converted to NA

Interpretation

Step 2: Allele balance

This represents the ratio of reads showing the reference allele to all reads. Expected ratio is 0.5, thus if there are large devisions this may indicate false heterozygotes due to coverage. This essentially filters for min and max heterozygosity.

vcf_filtered_AB <- filter_allele_balance(vcf_filtered, min.ratio = 0.25, max.ratio = 0.75)
## 20.85% of het genotypes (2.2% of all genotypes) fall outside of 0.25 - 0.75 allele balance ratio and were converted to NA

Step 3: Maximum depth per SNP

Removing SNPs with outlier depth values - will most likely remove SNPs that are spuriously mapped or paralogous loci.

## Visualize the max depth without setting any filters
max_depth(vcf_filtered)
## cutoff is not specified, exploratory visualization will be generated.

## dashed line indicates a mean depth across all SNPs of 13.6

We will set this to 22 to cut off the majority of the tail in the histogram (mean depth is 13.6)

vcf_filtered <- max_depth(vcf_filtered_AB, maxdepth = 22)
## maxdepth cutoff is specified, filtered vcfR object will be returned

## 4.19% of SNPs were above a mean depth of 22 and were removed from the vcf

Step 4: Minor allele count

We will then set MAC to 3 for the downstream analyses.

vcf_mac3 <- min_mac(vcf_filtered, min.mac = 3)

## 50.76% of SNPs fell below a minor allele count of 3 and were removed from the VCF
